<i>but also with deep bitterness.</i>

1473
01:53:03,157 --> 01:53:06,994
<i>"He said, " You want a separation?</i>

1474
01:53:07,078 --> 01:53:08,621
<i>What would you do all alone?"</i>

1475
01:53:08,704 --> 01:53:12,249
<i>And you answer, "Aren't I alone already?"</i>

1476
01:53:12,667 --> 01:53:14,251
<i>Go ahead.</i>

1477
01:53:14,335 --> 01:53:17,380
Guido, there's no doubt about this one.
She's perfect.

1478
01:53:23,177 --> 01:53:25,763
We've gone on like this for five months.

1479
01:53:26,180 --> 01:53:28,057
They're all so old.

1480
01:53:30,059 --> 01:53:31,268
<i>Fiuggi is carbonated.</i>

1481
01:53:31,352 --> 01:53:34,939
<i>No, it's the least sparkling. Louder.</i>

1482
01:53:35,022 --> 01:53:36,691
<i>Fine. Send up the Fiuggi.</i>

1483
01:53:36,774 --> 01:53:37,942
<i>Hang up the phone.</i>

1484
01:53:38,943 --> 01:53:40,945
<i>Screen test, Miss Olimpia.</i>

1485
01:53:41,821 --> 01:53:44,073
What about this one?

1486
01:53:44,156 --> 01:53:45,825
<i>More seductively.</i>

1487
01:53:45,908 --> 01:53:48,661
<i>It's dangerous leaving me alone.</i>

1488
01:53:49,370 --> 01:53:52,331
<i>- Why? What do you do?
- Should I repeat the line?</i>

1489
01:53:52,415 --> 01:53:54,041
<i>No, put down the phone.</i>

1490
01:53:54,917 --> 01:53:58,546
<i>Turn your head this way. Great. Cut.</i>

1491
01:53:59,463 --> 01:54:01,465
Luisa, where are you going?

1492
01:54:02,717 --> 01:54:05,261
Back to the hotel. I'm sleepy. Good night.

1493
01:54:05,344 --> 01:54:06,721
Wait a second. Listen.

1494
01:54:07,096 --> 01:54:08,514
What's wrong? What happened?

1495
01:54:08,597 --> 01:54:10,307
Nothing happened.

1496
01:54:10,391 --> 01:54:12,476
Nothing ever happens between you and me.

1497
01:54:13,853 --> 01:54:16,814
Did something you saw offend you?
It's just a movie.

1498
01:54:16,897 --> 01:54:19,692
Oh, I know that better than anyone.

1499
01:54:19,775 --> 01:54:22,111
Another fiction, another lie.

1500
01:54:22,194 --> 01:54:24,864
You put all of us in it,
but the way it suits you.

1501
01:54:24,947 --> 01:54:28,242
But the truth is something else entirely,
and only I know the truth.

1502
01:54:28,325 --> 01:54:30,661
You're lucky I'd never have the nerve

1503
01:54:30,745 --> 01:54:33,080
to make it public the way you do.

1504
01:54:33,164 --> 01:54:36,208
- Go on, make your movie!
- No, I won't.

1505
01:54:36,292 --> 01:54:38,753
Indulge yourself. Stroke your ego.

1506
01:54:39,628 --> 01:54:42,173
Make everyone think you're so wonderful.

1507
01:54:42,256 --> 01:54:44,633
But what could you have to say
to strangers

1508
01:54:44,717 --> 01:54:47,136
when you can't tell the truth
to the one closest to you,

1509
01:54:47,219 --> 01:54:48,697
the woman who's grown old at your side?

1510
01:54:48,721 --> 01:54:50,848
Luisa, cut the melodrama.

1511
01:54:53,517 --> 01:54:56,103
You were right to ask me to come.

1512
01:54:56,187 --> 01:54:58,981
We needed an ending.

1513
01:54:59,065 --> 01:55:01,692
I assure you, I won't be coming back.

1514
01:55:01,776 --> 01:55:03,235
You can go to hell!

1515
01:55:16,248 --> 01:55:20,086
<i>That's it. Run! Faster!</i>

1516
01:55:20,169 --> 01:55:22,338
<i>The man said to run!</i>

1517
01:55:22,421 --> 01:55:23,964
<i>You keep quiet!</i>

1518
01:55:25,716 --> 01:55:27,843
<i>Throw that ignoramus out!</i>

1519
01:55:27,927 --> 01:55:29,553
<i>Now sing, ma'am.</i>

1520
01:55:30,096 --> 01:55:34,809
You may say I'm losing my marbles,
but the figures are all right here.

1521
01:55:34,892 --> 01:55:38,395
No, I'll never pay this!
You are losing your marbles.

1522
01:55:38,479 --> 01:55:41,440
<i>Saraghina, look. We've got the money.</i>

1523
01:55:41,941 --> 01:55:44,110
<i>Saraghina, the rumba!</i>

1524
01:55:44,193 --> 01:55:47,571
Guido, would you please say something?

1525
01:55:49,323 --> 01:55:50,908
What about this one?

1526
01:55:51,867 --> 01:55:55,704
Frankly, I preferred the one before.
She's from Naples, isn't she?

1527
01:55:55,788 --> 01:55:59,875
Can't you see that I'm stammering?

1528
01:55:59,959 --> 01:56:03,420
<i>When are you coming? I'm tired of waiting.</i>

1529
01:56:03,504 --> 01:56:04,505
<i>Look at me.</i>

1530
01:56:04,588 --> 01:56:07,133
<i>Don't leave me alone.
You know it's dangerous.</i>

1531
01:56:07,216 --> 01:56:08,300
<i>Turn around.</i>

1532
01:56:08,384 --> 01:56:11,720
<i>Don't leave me alone.
You know it's dangerous, darling.</i>

1533
01:56:11,804 --> 01:56:12,805
<i>Look over here.</i>

1534
01:56:12,888 --> 01:56:16,559
<i>Why don't you come right away?
You're making me wait.</i>

1535
01:56:16,642 --> 01:56:18,769
<i>You know it's dangerous
when I have to wait.</i>

1536
01:56:18,853 --> 01:56:20,646
<i>Louder! Louder!</i>

1537
01:56:21,564 --> 01:56:23,607
<i>Countess, walk.</i>

1538
01:56:23,691 --> 01:56:25,484
<i>I said to walk.</i>

1539
01:56:25,568 --> 01:56:27,528
<i>Don't touch me with your hand.</i>

1540
01:56:29,113 --> 01:56:30,739
EVENING LIGHT

1541
01:56:32,199 --> 01:56:33,742
<i>Screen test one, Miss Grazia.</i>

1542
01:56:33,826 --> 01:56:35,661
<i>Bare your shoulders.</i>

1543
01:56:35,744 --> 01:56:39,248
<i>Saraghina, we've got the money.</i>

1544
01:56:39,790 --> 01:56:42,126
<i>Cut. Was that all right?</i>

1545
01:56:44,003 --> 01:56:46,839
Signora, what do you think?

1546
01:56:46,922 --> 01:56:49,258
Speak up. This is a democracy.

1547
01:56:49,341 --> 01:56:52,845
If he won't speak up, at least
you might say something. <i>Sacrebleu!</i>

1548
01:56:54,096 --> 01:56:57,892
You can't hide. We can find you anywhere.
How are you?

1549
01:56:57,975 --> 01:57:00,895
I'm Coletti, from Claudia's press agency.

1550
01:57:00,978 --> 01:57:04,398
We met 15 years ago. You remember me?

1551
01:57:04,481 --> 01:57:06,150
Look, she's here.

1552
01:57:06,233 --> 01:57:07,610
Where?

1553
01:57:13,449 --> 01:57:14,825
Excuse me.

1554
01:57:23,584 --> 01:57:24,668
Claudia.

1555
01:57:25,336 --> 01:57:27,296
- How are you?
- Fine. And you?

1556
01:57:28,547 --> 01:57:31,550
So you finally came.
Let's go outside, shall we?

1557
01:57:32,218 --> 01:57:34,261
This is Caroline, my secretary.

1558
01:57:36,847 --> 01:57:38,849
I'd like to speak to you alone.

1559
01:57:44,104 --> 01:57:47,066
- When do we start shooting?
- Very soon.

1560
01:57:47,149 --> 01:57:50,486
- What's my part?
- I'll tell you everything later.

1561
01:57:50,569 --> 01:57:52,404
I'm very happy to be working with you.

1562
01:57:52,488 --> 01:57:56,200
I hope I'll be of help.
But I want to know everything.

1563
01:57:57,284 --> 01:57:59,078
Where are we going now?

1564
01:58:08,337 --> 01:58:09,505
Well?

1565
01:58:11,507 --> 01:58:12,883
That way.

1566
01:58:28,941 --> 01:58:31,235
You're so beautiful. I'm tongue-tied.

1567
01:58:31,318 --> 01:58:33,612
You make my heart beat like a schoolboy's.

1568
01:58:34,863 --> 01:58:36,699
You don't believe me, do you?

1569
01:58:37,199 --> 01:58:39,868
You inspire true and deep respect.

1570
01:58:42,204 --> 01:58:44,623
Who do you love? Who do you care about?

1571
01:58:44,707 --> 01:58:45,874
You.

1572
01:58:49,169 --> 01:58:51,171
You've come just in time.

1573
01:58:52,298 --> 01:58:53,716
Why do you smile that way?

1574
01:58:53,799 --> 01:58:57,428
I never know if you're judging me,
forgiving me or mocking me.

1575
01:58:57,511 --> 01:58:58,512
I'm listening.

1576
01:58:58,595 --> 01:59:01,849
You said you'd tell me about the film.
I know nothing.

1577
01:59:08,147 --> 01:59:11,317
Could you leave everything behind
and start life all over again...

1578
01:59:13,235 --> 01:59:16,405
choose one thing only
and be faithful to it,

1579
01:59:16,488 --> 01:59:20,701
make it the reason for your existence,
the one thing that contains everything

1580
01:59:20,784 --> 01:59:22,953
because your dedication to it
makes it infinite?

1581
01:59:23,037 --> 01:59:24,413
Could you?

1582
01:59:26,332 --> 01:59:29,585
If I said to you, "Claudia"...

1583
01:59:32,254 --> 01:59:34,882
Which way are we going?
I don't know the way.

1584
01:59:35,674 --> 01:59:38,260
What about you? Could you?

1585
01:59:38,969 --> 01:59:42,681
The springs must be nearby.
Listen. Turn here.

1586
01:59:45,184 --> 01:59:47,811
No, this guy here couldn't do it.

1587
01:59:47,895 --> 01:59:50,022
He wants to grab everything and devour it.

1588
01:59:50,105 --> 01:59:52,107
He can't give up a single thing.

1589
01:59:52,191 --> 01:59:54,735
He changes direction every day
for fear of missing the path.

1590
01:59:54,818 --> 01:59:57,488
- He's slowly bleeding to death.
- Is this how the film ends?

1591
01:59:57,571 --> 01:59:58,864
No, this is how it starts.

1592
01:59:58,947 --> 02:00:01,033
Then he meets the girl at the springs,

1593
02:00:01,116 --> 02:00:03,535
one of those girls
who pass out the healing water.

1594
02:00:04,953 --> 02:00:06,163
She's beautiful...

1595
02:00:07,539 --> 02:00:09,083
both young and ancient,

1596
02:00:09,958 --> 02:00:12,878
a child and yet already a woman,
authentic and radiant.

1597
02:00:14,171 --> 02:00:16,965
There's no doubt that she's his salvation.

1598
02:00:17,758 --> 02:00:21,095
You'll be all in white,
your hair long, just as it is now.

1599
02:00:31,772 --> 02:00:33,065
Turn off the lights.

1600
02:01:11,937 --> 02:01:13,188
Now what?

1601
02:01:28,787 --> 02:01:30,414
Let's leave this place.

1602
02:01:32,124 --> 02:01:34,001
It makes me uneasy.

1603
02:01:34,084 --> 02:01:35,919
It doesn't seem real.

1604
02:01:36,003 --> 02:01:38,380
I really like it. Isn't that Odd?

1605
02:01:41,800 --> 02:01:45,345
I didn't understand much of your story.

1606
02:01:45,429 --> 02:01:49,600
A guy like your character,
who doesn't love anybody,

1607
02:01:49,683 --> 02:01:51,393
isn't very sympathetic, you know.

1608
02:01:53,395 --> 02:01:55,063
It's his fault.

1609
02:01:55,147 --> 02:01:57,316
What does he expect from other people?

1610
02:01:58,192 --> 02:02:00,486
You think I don't know that?

1611
02:02:01,278 --> 02:02:03,906
You're a pain like the others.

1612
02:02:03,989 --> 02:02:06,992
I see no one can tell you anything!

1613
02:02:07,075 --> 02:02:10,913
You're so funny in that big, ugly hat.
You look like an old man.

1614
02:02:13,624 --> 02:02:15,042
I don't understand.

1615
02:02:15,125 --> 02:02:20,255
He meets a new girl who can give him
new life, and he pushes her away?

1616
02:02:20,339 --> 02:02:22,341
Because he no longer believes in it.

1617
02:02:23,842 --> 02:02:25,761
Because he doesn't know how to love.

1618
02:02:25,844 --> 02:02:28,472
Because it's not true
that a woman can change a man.

1619
02:02:28,555 --> 02:02:29,995
Because he doesn't know how to love.

1620
02:02:30,057 --> 02:02:33,810
Above all, because I don't feel
like telling another pile of lies.

1621
02:02:33,894 --> 02:02:36,230
Because he doesn't know how to love.

1622
02:02:37,481 --> 02:02:40,359
I'm sorry for making you
come all the way here.

1623
02:02:40,442 --> 02:02:41,693
Forgive me.

1624
02:02:42,402 --> 02:02:44,613
You're such a phony.

1625
02:02:44,696 --> 02:02:46,698
So there's no part in the film.

1626
02:02:47,616 --> 02:02:50,911
You're right. There's no part.

1627
02:02:50,994 --> 02:02:53,038
And there's no film.

1628
02:02:53,121 --> 02:02:55,165
There's nothing anywhere.

1629
02:02:55,541 --> 02:02:58,919
And as far as I'm concerned,
it can all end right here.

1630
02:03:04,550 --> 02:03:07,302
Here they are!

1631
02:03:07,386 --> 02:03:10,222
Where did you go?
We're starting next week.

1632
02:03:10,305 --> 02:03:12,474
Your producer had a great idea.

1633
02:03:12,558 --> 02:03:16,436
The greatest cocktail party
to ever launch a movie.

1634
02:03:16,520 --> 02:03:18,647
The launchpad, tomorrow afternoon.

1635
02:03:18,730 --> 02:03:20,041
Radio, television, the foreign press.

1636
02:03:20,065 --> 02:03:22,067
Guido, we're starting for real.

1637
02:03:47,467 --> 02:03:48,844
Grab him!

1638
02:03:55,767 --> 02:03:57,519
Come on, walk!

1639
02:03:57,603 --> 02:03:59,354
I want to go home.

1640
02:03:59,438 --> 02:04:01,023
Come on!

1641
02:04:01,106 --> 02:04:02,899
Here he is!

1642
02:04:09,615 --> 02:04:12,326
Guido, where are you going?
It's over here!

1643
02:04:17,372 --> 02:04:20,334
Mr. Guido, I'm sure today
will be a beautiful...

1644
02:04:26,923 --> 02:04:30,552
I'm very curious
to finally hear the story.

1645
02:04:30,636 --> 02:04:34,264
Don't you take yourself
a bit too seriously, Mr. Anselmo?

1646
02:04:41,313 --> 02:04:44,024
Leave me alone! I can walk by myself!

1647
02:04:48,528 --> 02:04:51,323
Hello, and good luck!

1648
02:04:53,867 --> 02:04:55,702
<i>Commendatore</i>, here he is!

1649
02:04:59,164 --> 02:05:02,459
We've been waiting for you for three days.

1650
02:05:02,542 --> 02:05:05,170
- It's winter already.
- Attention, please.

1651
02:05:11,134 --> 02:05:13,804
Do you think pornography is an art form?

1652
02:05:13,887 --> 02:05:17,432
Is pornography
the most intense form of entertainment?

1653
02:05:19,059 --> 02:05:21,645
Why don't you ever make a film about love?

1654
02:05:33,907 --> 02:05:37,202
-I wish to announce that —
-Tomorrow, tomorrow.

1655
02:05:37,869 --> 02:05:39,371
What do you think you can teach us?

1656
02:05:39,454 --> 02:05:41,599
Do you really think your life
can be of interest to others?

1657
02:05:41,623 --> 02:05:44,751
Can you honestly admit
you have nothing to say?

1658
02:05:51,967 --> 02:05:55,846
He'll now speak to you directly.

1659
02:05:57,806 --> 02:05:59,057
Answer.

1660
02:05:59,141 --> 02:06:00,517
Go on.

1661
02:06:01,351 --> 02:06:03,228
Guido, say something.

1662
02:06:03,311 --> 02:06:06,314
Anything at all. Do it for me.

1663
02:06:09,109 --> 02:06:10,610
I promise you an art film!

1664
02:06:10,694 --> 02:06:14,364
If this film flops, what will you live on?

1665
02:06:14,448 --> 02:06:17,242
Are you for or against divorce?
Tell me honestly.

1666
02:06:22,789 --> 02:06:25,917
Your questions betray a certain hostility.

1667
02:06:26,001 --> 02:06:27,854
I assure you that my director
is in great form...

1668
02:06:27,878 --> 02:06:29,838
What am I supposed to do?

1669
02:06:29,921 --> 02:06:32,758
And should be treated with respect.

1670
02:06:32,841 --> 02:06:35,761
Conocchia, forgive me
if I treated you badly.

1671
02:06:35,844 --> 02:06:38,555
You were wonderful, the best of them all.

1672
02:06:38,638 --> 02:06:41,349
He ponders, considers, reflects.

1673
02:06:41,433 --> 02:06:42,517
Say something.

1674
02:06:42,601 --> 02:06:45,604
I've been paying for your confusion
and crises for months.

1675
02:06:45,687 --> 02:06:48,440
Quit this film and I'll ruin you.

1676
02:06:48,523 --> 02:06:51,443
He'll now be at your disposal.

1677
02:06:51,526 --> 02:06:53,445
Claudia, where are you?

1678
02:06:53,528 --> 02:06:55,614
Rossella, where are your spirits now?

1679
02:06:57,449 --> 02:06:59,701
What should I do? Leave you? Disappear?

1680
02:06:59,785 --> 02:07:02,454
You'll never be what you once were.

1681
02:07:02,537 --> 02:07:05,457
I'll no longer be your wife.
When will you truly marry me?

1682
02:07:05,540 --> 02:07:09,461
Luisa, do you really want a separation?

1683
02:07:09,544 --> 02:07:11,421
How can I go on like this till the end?

1684
02:07:11,505 --> 02:07:13,965
What does your wife think?

1685
02:07:18,220 --> 02:07:20,180
In your right-hand pocket.

1686
02:07:20,931 --> 02:07:22,307
So long, Guido.

1687
02:07:22,390 --> 02:07:24,559
I put it in your right-hand pocket.

1688
02:07:33,610 --> 02:07:36,571
No, nobody gets away with that!

1689
02:07:36,655 --> 02:07:38,240
Buffoon!

1690
02:07:38,323 --> 02:07:39,324
Lunatic!

1691
02:07:39,407 --> 02:07:41,868
Get out here, you coward!

1692
02:07:42,536 --> 02:07:45,747
Just a minute.
I'm thinking of what to say.

1693
02:07:45,831 --> 02:07:47,541
That's it!

1694
02:07:47,624 --> 02:07:49,876
I'm coming. I'm coming.

1695
02:07:52,295 --> 02:07:54,881
He's an incurable romantic.

1696
02:07:59,344 --> 02:08:01,972
Where are you running off to,
you naughty boy?

1697
02:08:19,990 --> 02:08:22,742
Take it all down, boys. This film is off.

1698
02:08:22,826 --> 02:08:26,121
It has to be gone in two days.
Start right away.

1699
02:08:26,204 --> 02:08:28,874
Get going. Tear it all down.
Right, <i>Dottore</i>?

1700
02:08:28,957 --> 02:08:31,585
Yes, thanks. So long, boys.

1701
02:08:31,668 --> 02:08:33,044
See you on another film.

1702
02:08:33,128 --> 02:08:34,671
Let's hope so.

1703
02:08:39,843 --> 02:08:41,428
So long, sailor.

1704
02:08:45,432 --> 02:08:46,808
You did the right thing.

1705
02:08:46,892 --> 02:08:49,352
Believe me, today is a good day for you.

1706
02:08:50,103 --> 02:08:52,647
These are tough decisions, I know.

1707
02:08:52,731 --> 02:08:56,651
But we intellectuals — and I say "we"
because I consider you one...

1708
02:08:56,735 --> 02:08:59,821
Must remain clear-headed right to the end.

1709
02:08:59,905 --> 02:09:02,782
There are so many superfluous things
in the world already.

1710
02:09:02,866 --> 02:09:04,951
No need to add chaos to chaos.

1711
02:09:06,703 --> 02:09:10,248
Besides, losing money
is part of a producer's job.

1712
02:09:11,708 --> 02:09:14,210
I congratulate you. You had no choice.

1713
02:09:14,294 --> 02:09:16,254
He got what he deserved

1714
02:09:16,338 --> 02:09:20,175
for embarking on such a frivolous venture
so lightheartedly.

1715
02:09:22,177 --> 02:09:24,596
No need for nostalgia or remorse.

1716
02:09:24,679 --> 02:09:26,097
Destroying is better than creating

1717
02:09:26,181 --> 02:09:28,516
when we're not creating
those few truly necessary things.

1718
02:09:29,476 --> 02:09:32,687
But is there anything
so just and true in this world

1719
02:09:32,771 --> 02:09:34,856
that it has the right to live?

1720
02:09:35,815 --> 02:09:38,777
For him, a bad film
is merely a financial matter,

1721
02:09:38,860 --> 02:09:42,030
but for you, at this point,
it could have been the end.

1722
02:09:43,073 --> 02:09:45,825
Better to knock it all down
and strew the ground with salt,

1723
02:09:45,909 --> 02:09:49,663
as the ancients did
to purify the battlefields.

1724
02:09:49,746 --> 02:09:51,915
In the end, what we need

1725
02:09:51,998 --> 02:09:55,627
is some hygiene,
cleanliness, disinfection.

1726
02:09:56,127 --> 02:10:00,632
We're smothered
by words, images and sounds

1727
02:10:00,715 --> 02:10:02,801
that have no right to exist,

1728
02:10:02,884 --> 02:10:06,054
that come from the void
and return to the void.

1729
02:10:06,137 --> 02:10:09,015
Of any artist truly deserving of the name,

1730
02:10:09,099 --> 02:10:12,185
we should ask nothing
but this act of faith...

1731
02:10:12,268 --> 02:10:14,229
To learn silence.

1732
02:10:14,312 --> 02:10:16,898
Remember Mallarme's homage
to the white page?

1733
02:10:16,982 --> 02:10:18,817
Guido, wait!

1734
02:10:21,236 --> 02:10:23,780
We're ready to begin. Hello, sir.

1735
02:10:26,783 --> 02:10:28,034
All my best wishes!

1736
02:10:28,118 --> 02:10:32,372
If we can't have everything,
nothingness is true perfection.

1737
02:10:32,455 --> 02:10:35,125
Forgive me
for making all these references,

1738
02:10:35,208 --> 02:10:38,003
but we critics do what we can.

1739
02:10:38,086 --> 02:10:42,716
Our true mission is to sweep away
the thousands of miscarriages

1740
02:10:42,799 --> 02:10:44,843
that try every day, obscenely,

1741
02:10:44,926 --> 02:10:46,594
to come into this world.

1742
02:10:47,429 --> 02:10:52,392
And you would actually leave behind you
a whole film,

1743
02:10:52,475 --> 02:10:56,104
like a cripple leaving behind
his crooked footprint.

1744
02:10:56,771 --> 02:11:00,650
What monstrous presumption
to think that others could benefit

1745
02:11:00,734 --> 02:11:03,737
from the squalid catalog of your mistakes.

1746
02:11:04,446 --> 02:11:06,948
What do you gain by stringing together

1747
02:11:07,032 --> 02:11:09,909
the tattered pieces of your life,
the vague memories,

1748
02:11:09,993 --> 02:11:13,705
the faces of those you could never love?

1749
02:11:22,380 --> 02:11:24,924
<i>What is this sudden happiness
that makes me tremble,</i>

1750
02:11:25,008 --> 02:11:27,594
<i>that gives me strength and life?</i>

1751
02:11:28,178 --> 02:11:30,138
<i>Forgive me, sweet creatures.</i>

1752
02:11:30,221 --> 02:11:32,474
<i>I didn't understand. I didn't know.</i>

1753
02:11:33,016 --> 02:11:35,894
<i>How right it is to accept you,
to love you.</i>

1754
02:11:35,977 --> 02:11:37,645
<i>And how simple.</i>

1755
02:11:38,146 --> 02:11:41,649
<i>Luisa, I feel like I've been set free.</i>

1756
02:11:41,733 --> 02:11:43,777
<i>Everything seems so good, so meaningful.</i>

1757
02:11:43,860 --> 02:11:45,320
<i>Everything is true.</i>

1758
02:11:45,403 --> 02:11:47,947
<i>I wish I could explain,</i>

1759
02:11:48,031 --> 02:11:49,908
<i>but I don't know how.</i>

1760
02:11:50,909 --> 02:11:55,663
<i>Now everything's all confused once again,
like it was before.</i>

1761
02:11:55,747 --> 02:11:58,291
<i>But this confusion is me,</i>

1762
02:11:58,374 --> 02:12:01,044
<i>as I am, not like I'd like to be.</i>

1763
02:12:01,127 --> 02:12:05,090
<i>I'm no longer afraid
of telling the truth —.</i>

1764
02:12:05,173 --> 02:12:08,593
<i>About what I don't know, what
I'm looking for, what I haven't found.</i>

1765
02:12:09,052 --> 02:12:10,804
<i>Only this way do I feel alive.</i>

1766
02:12:10,887 --> 02:12:13,890
<i>Only this way can I look
into your faithful eyes without shame.</i>

1767
02:12:14,349 --> 02:12:17,852
<i>Life is a celebration.
Let's live it together.</i>

1768
02:12:18,770 --> 02:12:21,564
<i>That's all I can say, Luisa,
to you and all the others.</i>

1769
02:12:21,648 --> 02:12:24,025
<i>Accept me for what I am, if you can.</i>

1770
02:12:24,109 --> 02:12:26,694
<i>It's the only way
we might find each other.</i>

1771
02:12:27,946 --> 02:12:30,698
I don't know if what you've said is right,

1772
02:12:30,782 --> 02:12:33,660
but I can try if you help me.

1773
02:12:51,094 --> 02:12:53,888
Welcome back. Follow me.

1774
02:13:33,344 --> 02:13:35,763
Just a minute. I'll give the signal.

1775
02:13:46,024 --> 02:13:47,442
There.

1776
02:13:47,525 --> 02:13:49,444
Now go to the curtain.

1777
02:13:58,661 --> 02:14:00,121
Open it.

1778
02:14:01,915 --> 02:14:03,875
Everyone come down.

1779
02:14:03,958 --> 02:14:06,586
Talk to each other.

1780
02:14:57,845 --> 02:14:59,264
Mama.

1781
02:15:04,352 --> 02:15:05,478
Sgulp!

1782
02:15:06,688 --> 02:15:09,691
I understand what you meant.
You can't do without us.

1783
02:15:10,525 --> 02:15:13,945
- What time will you call tomorrow?
- Fine, fine. Now join the line.

1784
02:15:14,445 --> 02:15:15,571
Maurice!

1785
02:15:19,617 --> 02:15:21,369
Come quickly! Stop fooling around.

1786
02:15:22,328 --> 02:15:25,415
Everybody hold hands!

1787
02:15:25,498 --> 02:15:26,791
Spread out!

1788
02:15:26,874 --> 02:15:29,002
All together!

1789
02:15:31,296 --> 02:15:32,588
Maestro!

1790
02:15:32,672 --> 02:15:34,966
Everyone hold hands!

